this is a summary about the first video 
git helps us manage our projects files
by keeping track of changes (nothing is ever lost)
collaboration without having to lose track of our own work and without waiting for somebody to finish
feature branches implementing multiple tasks - best example to this is a tree branch if theres two task in one project that we want to finish then we can create two branches and we can merge it after we are done with either of them or both when we want to
git industry standard - its already assumed that a developer knows all about git so it's required by the industry 